VAIFORM — FFMPEG / FINALIZE / WORKER RULES

Applies to:
- src/utils/ffmpeg*.js
- story-finalize.worker.js
- src/services/story-finalize.*
- src/services/story.service.js when finalize/render behavior is touched

Rules:
- Do not change render/finalize semantics casually.
- Before modifying ffmpeg/finalize behavior, audit:
  - current caller-backed render path
  - finalize/runtime docs
  - current service/worker ownership
- Preserve portrait/render invariants unless explicitly changing them with evidence.
- Do not weaken queue/admission/idempotency/settlement behavior.
- If touching filter graph generation, summarize intended graph/arg changes before implementing.
- If touching finalize contract behavior, update owning canonical docs first.
